@endnode



@node "INSTALLATION" "Amiga Webcam Software (Installation)"

                       @{b}I N S T A L L A T I O N@{ub}

 
 Copy the AWS directory to your harddrive.

 Before you start this program for the first time, you should adapt the tooltypes 
 of the AWS icon to your configuration:


 DEVICE=serial.device
 UNIT=0

 If you want to use the internal serial port set device to serial.device and unit to 0,
 otherwise select the driver and unit of your serial board.


 BPS=230400

 Set the speed of your serial port.
 You can use 57600 for the internal serial port,
 but higher values (e.g. 115200 or 230400) for serial boards.


 USERNAME=
 PASSWORD=

 The username and password to use when logging in.

 PORT=21 

 The remote port to connect.
 This tooltype is optional, by default the program will use port 21.


 HOSTDIR=

 The site and dir to send the photo.
 The hostdir argument must be in usual URL form.
 Don't enter ftp://



  
@endnode



@node "USAGE" "Amiga Webcam Software (Usage)"

                       @{b}U S A G E@{ub}

 Just start the program and click on the START WEBCAM button.
 If the program fails then take a look at the log files in Ram to see what goes wrong.
 

 
 To watch your webcam you could use a program from Aminet (Webcam.lha)
 If you want to use a browser to watch the webcam you need to upload the included html document.
 


  
@endnode





